    "content": "\n<p>When we started working with a data-rich but report-poor company, the technology wasn't the problem. The manual effort between the systems was. This is how we turned that friction into an automated workflow — and what it changed.</p>\n<h2>The Problem</h2>\n<ul><li>Existing SAP, ERP and BI tools, yet weekly manual reporting</li><li>~23 hours a week spent collecting and reconciling data</li><li>Decisions waiting on reports and meetings</li><li>No way to just ask a question and get an answer</li></ul>\n<h2>What We Automated</h2>\n<p>Rather than rip out the tools the team already relied on, we connected them with AI agents that handle the repetitive work end to end:</p>\n<h3>Automated extraction</h3><p>Data is pulled from SAP, emails, trackers and business systems.</p><h3>Cleaning and validation</h3><p>The pipeline standardises and checks data automatically.</p><h3>Continuous dashboards</h3><p>Reports refresh themselves — no manual pulls.</p><h3>Ask-anything queries</h3><p>Leaders ask 'show product-wise performance for 30 days' and get an instant answer.</p>\n<h2>The Results</h2>\n<ul><li>Reporting effort cut from ~23 hours a week to under 2</li><li>Same-day decisions instead of week-old reports</li><li>A single source of truth across departments</li><li>Analysts freed to analyse, not assemble</li></ul>\n<h2>Why It Matters</h2>\n<p>When every business event becomes data and every data point becomes an insight, companies move faster and decide better.</p>\n<h2>Could This Work in Your Business?</h2>\n<p>If you're already running a CRM, ERP, WhatsApp or any business software, there's a good chance you're using a fraction of its potential — and losing hours to the gaps between systems. In a free 30-minute AI automation audit, we map your workflows and show you exactly where time and money are leaking, and what to automate first. You keep the plan either way. <a href=\"/#contact-form\">Book your free automation audit</a>.</p>\n",
